CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1966, pg. 13A reads: "Rainbow Cotillion - One of the holiday season's prettiest affairs was a Rainbow Cotillion in the ballroom of the George Washington Hotel in Washington, Pa. The event was sponsored by the Civic League of Washington and proceeds aided the Lemoyne Community Center..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two men, and twelve women, one wearing dark v-neck dress and fur stole, gathered in George Washington Hotel for Rainbow Cotillion, Washington, Pennsylvania
